io.storj

Class Bucket

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.storj.Bucket
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public class Bucket
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    Represents a stateful resource to a bucket in a project. It allows executing operations on the bucket like listing, uploading, downloading, and deleting objects.

    Make sure to always close the Bucket object after completing work with it. The Bucket class implements the AutoCloseable interface, so it is best to use Bucket objects in try-with-resource blocks:

      try (Uplink uplink = new Uplink();
       Project project = uplink.openProject(scope);
       Bucket bucket = project.openBucket("my-bucket", scope)) {
      ...
  }
